Just follow these simple steps, with 2 commands only, for resetting root password in Ubuntu (provided that, you should know the machine login correctly):

1. Open Terminal : Press Ctrl + Alt + T
2. Type this command : sudo -i
3. Enter your machine login password correctly for '[sudo] password for user:'
4. Type this command : passwd root
5. 'Enter new Unix Password :' xxxxxxxx
6. 'Retype new Unix Password :' xxxxxxxx
7. You'll see : 'passwd : password updated successfully.'

Done!
